Credits and third-party components
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

partclone — https://partclone.org  (GPL-2.0-or-later)
    The filesystem-aware imaging engine that does the real backup and restore
    work. This project invokes partclone as an external program; it does not
    include or modify partclone's source. partclone's "or-later" clause permits
    its use alongside this GPL-3.0 project.

Arch Linux Tweak Tool (ATT) by Erik Dubois — https://www.arcolinux.com  (GPL-3.0)
    The look and feel of the GTK4 interface, the pkexec/Wayland launcher
    pattern, the in-app toast notification, and several CSS values are modelled
    on ATT. With thanks to Erik Dubois and the ArcoLinux community.

mintstick by Clement Lefebvre / Linux Mint — https://github.com/linuxmint/mintstick  (GPL-2.0-or-later)
    The USB Writer's format backend (usb-format.sh) follows mintstick's approach:
    zero the start of the disk, write a fresh msdos table and one primary
    partition, clear old signatures with wipefs, then mkfs. This project does not
    include mintstick's source. mintstick's "or-later" clause permits its use
    alongside this GPL-3.0 project.

zstd — https://github.com/facebook/zstd
    Compression of the partition images.

smartmontools — https://www.smartmontools.org  (GPL-2.0-or-later)
    The SMART health pre-flight invokes `smartctl` (JSON output) to read each
    disk's health. This project calls it as an external program; it does not
    include or modify smartmontools' source.

GNU ddrescue — https://www.gnu.org/software/ddrescue/  (GPL-2.0-or-later)
    The Rescue page's failing-disk salvage engine; this project invokes
    `ddrescue` and `ddrescuelog` as external programs and does not include or
    modify their source. (Packaged as `gddrescue` on Debian/Ubuntu.)

GTK 4 / PyGObject
    The graphical toolkit and Python bindings.
